## Project Structure

```
src/
  client.ts          # Main client class
  http-client.ts     # HTTP layer with retry logic
  auth.ts            # OAuth 2.0 implementation
  pagination.ts      # Async pagination iterator
  errors.ts          # Error class hierarchy
  resources/         # One file per API resource
  types/             # TypeScript interfaces and enums
tests/               # Unit tests (vitest)
  integration/       # Integration tests
docs/                # API documentation per resource
```

## Key Patterns

- All methods are async and return Promises
- Request bodies use typed interfaces
- Path parameters are passed as the first argument object
- Query parameters (filters, pagination) are passed as optional second argument
- Binary uploads/downloads use `Buffer` or `ReadableStream`

